# ==========================================================================
#
#               Boundary Conditions Configuration File
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
#   Description:
#   This file specifies the boundary conditions for each face of the
#   computational domain.
#
#   Format:
#   <Face> <General_Type> <Specific_Handler> [param1=value1] ...
#
#   - Face:           Identifies the boundary face
#                     (-Xi, +Xi, -Eta, +Eta, -Zeta, +Zeta)
#   - General_Type:   Primary classification (e.g., INLET, OUTLET, WALL)
#   - Specific_Handler: The specific algorithm to apply (e.g., noslip)
#   - Parameters:     Optional key-value pairs for the handler
#
# ==========================================================================


# ==========================================================================
# 1. Inlet / Outlet Conditions
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Defines the flow conditions at the domain's entrances and exits.
# ==========================================================================

# An inlet on the -Zeta face with a constant velocity profile.
-Zeta   INLET    constant_velocity   vx=0.0 vy=0.0 vz=1.0

# An outlet on the +Zeta face that enforces global mass conservation.
+Zeta   OUTLET   conservation


# ==========================================================================
# 2. Wall Conditions
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Defines the behavior of the solid boundaries.
# ==========================================================================

# Stationary, no-slip walls on the +/- Eta and +/- Xi faces.
-Eta    WALL     noslip
+Eta    WALL     noslip
-Xi     WALL     noslip
+Xi     WALL     noslip


# ==========================================================================
# 3. Disabled & Example Configurations
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This section contains commented-out examples and previously used
# settings for reference. These lines are currently inactive.
# ==========================================================================

